Package com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api.expression

Interface Summary
ArrayElementAccess This PrimaryExpression type represents the access to a static array's element like 'anyPrimaryExpression.arrayIdentifier[anyOffsetExpression]', where 'anyPrimaryExpression' is an optional qualifier and 'arrayIdentifier' the identifier of the static array.
ArrayTypeDeclarator This PrimaryExpression type represents an array type declarator.
BinaryOperatorExpression This Expression type represents all kinds of binary operator expressions.
ClassConstructorCall This PrimaryExpression type represents a new expression via a class constructor invocation, i.e. something like 'new AnyClassType(constructorArgs)'.
ConditionalExpression This Expression type represents a conditional expression, i.e.
DotExpression This PrimaryExpression type represents a chain of primary expressions separated by dots.
ExplicitConstructorCall This PrimaryExpression type represents an explicit this or super constructor call.
Expression This JSOM type is the base type for all kinds of expressions.
Identifier This PrimaryExpression type represents a simple identifier expression, i.e. such an expression is nothing else than a not qualified identifier.
InstanceofExpression This Expression type represents an instanceof expression
Literal This PrimaryExpression represents a literal.
MethodCall This PrimaryExpression type represents a method invocation.
ParenthesizedExpression This Expression type represents a parenthesized expression, i.e.
PrimaryExpression This JSOM type is the base type for all kinds of expressions that are not of arithmetic or logical nature; i.e. a primary expression represents things like literals, method calls, new expressions, and so on.
PrimaryExpressionKeyword This PrimaryExpression type represents the most trivial kinds of primary expressions which are the keywords class, this , super or void.
StaticArrayCreator This PrimaryExpression type represents a new expression for creating static arrays.
TypeCast This Expression type represents a type cast.
UnaryOperatorExpression This Expression type represents all kinds of unary operator expressions.
